<%# Phase 27 follow-up (2026-05-17 + 2026-05-18) — Bundle games pane
    (formerly the Collection games pane).

    Turbo Frame fragment that fills the `/games` bundles modal. Slice 3
    of the modal revamp (2026-05-17) replaced the flat wrapping grid of
    cover tiles with a CSS-positioned composite that mirrors the libvips
    composite-cover layout. Up to nine games render as percentage-
    positioned anchors over a 3:4 canvas (cells supplied by
    `Composite::CellMap.for(n)`, the same source of truth the libvips
    renderer uses — so a layout edit propagates to both surfaces for
    free).

    The 1-game case falls out naturally: `Composite::CellMap.for(1)`
    returns a single cell at `(0, 0, 1, 1)` so the lone cover fills the
    canvas without a special branch here.

    2026-05-18 (slice W5) — the +N-more overflow shelf that used to sit
    below the composite is REPLACED with a flat "all games" table
    (`Bundles::AllGamesTableComponent`). Fixed copy "all games" (no
    `+N` count), zebra-striped `.sessions-table`-styled table listing
    EVERY member game with columns: checkbox, title, primary genre,
    short release date, rating-score chip. The composite cover grid at
    the top is intentionally untouched in this slice — only the bottom
    overflow section changes.

    2026-05-18 (Bug 1 fix) — the "all games" section now renders
    UNCONDITIONALLY so the `[+]` add-member trigger is always
    reachable, even on freshly-created (zero-member) bundles. The
    composite cover grid is still gated on `@games.any?` because an
    empty composite would just be blank canvas; the per-bundle
    fallback in the shelf tile covers the no-cover case there.

    Empty state: the `AllGamesTableComponent` renders a muted single-
    row "no games yet — click [+] to add" inside the table body when
    the bundle has no members. No JS confirm / alert / prompt.
%>
<%= turbo_frame_tag "bundles_modal_frame" do %>
  <% if @games.any? %>
    <%# 2026-05-18 — CSS-positioned composite cover grid is now owned
        by `Bundles::ModalCompositeComponent`. The component pulls
        `bundle.games.first(9)` and renders each cell over a 3:4 canvas
        using `Composite::CellMap.for(n)` — the same source of truth
        the libvips JPEG builder uses. %>
    <%= render Bundles::ModalCompositeComponent.new(bundle: @bundle) %>
  <% else %>
    <%# 2026-05-18 (EQ Bug 1 follow-up) — empty-bundle placeholder.
        Mirrors the populated composite slot above: same `width: 100%`
        + `aspect-ratio: 3 / 4` outer box, same 1px solid theme-aware
        border + 2px radius. Reuses the shelf-tile netflix-3 grid
        markup so the visual reads as "bundle waiting for members"
        rather than empty whitespace above the [+] add row. The
        `--modal` modifier lifts the controller-icon max-width caps so
        the SVGs scale proportionally at the modal's larger size
        instead of looking lost in oversized cells. %>
    <div class="bundle-tile__nocover-netflix3 bundle-tile__nocover-netflix3--modal"
         aria-label="<%= @bundle.name %>"
         title="<%= @bundle.name %>">
      <div class="cell cell--main">
        <%= image_tag image_path("controller_icon_light.svg"),
                      alt: "", loading: "lazy",
                      data: { theme: "light" },
                      class: "bundle-tile__nocover-icon bundle-tile__nocover-icon--large game-cover-fallback--light" %>
        <%= image_tag image_path("controller_icon_dark.svg"),
                      alt: "", loading: "lazy",
                      data: { theme: "dark" },
                      class: "bundle-tile__nocover-icon bundle-tile__nocover-icon--large game-cover-fallback--dark" %>
      </div>
      <div class="cell">
        <%= image_tag image_path("controller_icon_light.svg"),
                      alt: "", loading: "lazy",
                      data: { theme: "light" },
                      class: "bundle-tile__nocover-icon bundle-tile__nocover-icon--small game-cover-fallback--light" %>
        <%= image_tag image_path("controller_icon_dark.svg"),
                      alt: "", loading: "lazy",
                      data: { theme: "dark" },
                      class: "bundle-tile__nocover-icon bundle-tile__nocover-icon--small game-cover-fallback--dark" %>
      </div>
      <div class="cell">
        <%= image_tag image_path("controller_icon_light.svg"),
                      alt: "", loading: "lazy",
                      data: { theme: "light" },
                      class: "bundle-tile__nocover-icon bundle-tile__nocover-icon--small game-cover-fallback--light" %>
        <%= image_tag image_path("controller_icon_dark.svg"),
                      alt: "", loading: "lazy",
                      data: { theme: "dark" },
                      class: "bundle-tile__nocover-icon bundle-tile__nocover-icon--small game-cover-fallback--dark" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <%= render(Bundles::AllGamesTableComponent.new(bundle: @bundle)) %>
<% end %>
